        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 9 at 4:15PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 415 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Boomer, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
North Wilkesboro...
Wilkesboro...
Boomer...
Moravian Falls...
Fairplains...
and Cricket.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for
northwestern North Carolina.</instruction>
